LVM Storage Linux
## 🚀 Setup & Usage

### Prerequisites
- Ubuntu 20.04+ (or any RHEL/Debian-based distro)
- LVM2 package installed
- At least one additional raw disk attached (e.g. via VMware)

### Install LVM2
```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install lvm2 -y
```

### Step 1 — Create Physical Volume
```bash
# Initialise disk as a physical volume
sudo pvcreate /dev/sdb
sudo pvdisplay
```

### Step 2 — Create Volume Group
```bash
# Group physical volumes together
sudo vgcreate vg_data /dev/sdb
sudo vgdisplay
```

### Step 3 — Create Logical Volume
```bash
# Carve out a logical volume from the group
sudo lvcreate -L 10G -n lv_data vg_data

# Format it
sudo mkfs.ext4 /dev/vg_data/lv_data

# Mount it
sudo mkdir -p /mnt/data
sudo mount /dev/vg_data/lv_data /mnt/data
```

### Step 4 — Extend Volume Online (no downtime!)
```bash
# Add 5GB to existing volume while mounted
sudo lvextend -L +5G /dev/vg_data/lv_data
sudo resize2fs /dev/vg_data/lv_data

# Verify
df -h /mnt/data
```

### Step 5 — Create a Snapshot
```bash
sudo lvcreate -L 2G -s -n lv_data_snap /dev/vg_data/lv_data
sudo lvdisplay /dev/vg_data/lv_data_snap
```

